\pard\fi-426\li426\b 4.\tab REQUIRED SOFTWARE\b0\par
\par
\pard\li426 The following software is required to compile the DFU source code:\par
\par
\b Microsoft Windows\b0\par
\par
\pard\li710 This source code has been developed and tested on Microsoft Windows \f1 2000\f0  with Service Pack \f1 3\f0  installed, but it may be possible to build the software on other platforms.\par
\par
On Windows 2000 and Windows XP it is necessary to set the \b COPYCMD\b0  environment variable to \b /Y\b0 . This restores the Windows NT 4.0 behaviour of \b XCOPY\b0 , allowing the software to build correctly.\par
\par
The resulting executables have been tested on Windows 98, Windows ME, \f1 Windows NT 4, \f0 Windows 2000 and Windows XP. Note that the software does not work on earlier versions of Windows (such as Windows 95) due to the lack of support for required serial API calls.\par
\pard\li426\par
\b Microsoft Visual C++\b0\par
\par
\pard\li710 This source code has been developed and tested using Microsoft Visual C++ 6.0 Enterprise Edition with Service Pack 5 installed, but it may also be possible to build the software with other versions.\par
\par
Note that the 'VC++ MFC and Template Libraries' must be installed, and updated with at least Service Pack 3.\par
\pard\li426\par
\b Microsoft Platform SDK - Core SDK\b0\par
\par
\pard\li710 The code has been developed and tested using the Microsoft Platform SDK - Core SDK, November 2001 Edition (Build 5.1.3590.2), but other versions may be suitable.\par
\par
Only the 'Build environment' component is required; it is not necessary to install the complete SDK.\par
\par
After installation, the 'Register PSDK Directories with Visual Studio' shortcut should be run from the Start menu. Visual C++ should then be started and the \b Microsoft SDK\\include\b0  directory moved to appear \i after\i0  the \b VC98\b0  include directories. This is necessary to enable a modified version of the MFC 4.2 library to be built as described below.\par
\par
The Microsoft Platform SDK is available for free download from:\par
\pard\li994\ul http://www.microsoft.com/msdownload/platformsdk/sdkupdate\ulnone\par
\pard\li710\par
\pard\li426\b AVIQuick\b0\par
\par
\pard\li710 The AVI animations used within the DFU Wizard application were created with AVIQuick version 1.0. This tool can also be used to extract the individual frames of the animations to allow further editing.\par
\par
