\b 5.\tab COMPILATION\b0\par
\par
\pard\li426 Either two or three Visual Studio projects are included in this source code distribution, any combination of which may be installed and compiled:\par
\par
\b DFU Engine DLL\b0\par
\par
\pard\li710 The DFU Engine DLL implements the Device Firmware Upgrade procedure for BlueCore modules. It is used by the DFU Wizard application and DFU Tool Tips shell extension.\par
\par
The source code for this project is not normally supplied; the resulting DLL is supplied pre-built in binary form with the single header file required for its use.\par
\pard\li426\par
\b DFU Wizard GUI\b0\par
\par
\pard\li710 The BlueCore Device Firmware Upgrade Wizard is a sample user interface for the DFU Engine DLL. It can be easily customised and rebranded with a different look and feel.\par
\pard\li426\par
\b DFU Tool Tips DLL\b0\par
\par
\pard\li710 The DFU Tool Tips DLL is a Windows shell extension. It provides tool tips for DFU files within Windows Explorer windows, and adds options to the file's context menu to launch the DFU Wizard GUI.\par
\pard\li426\par
Shortcuts to the \b .dsw\b0  files for each of the installed projects are added to the Start menu during installation of the source code. To build a particular project simply load the relevant workspace into Visual Studio, make the appropriate project active, select the Debug or Release build, and press F7.\par
\par
The output files from all projects are placed in the \b result\\bin\\release\b0  or \b result\\bin\\debug\b0  directory as appropriate. \f1 A s\f0 hortcut to open \f1 a \f0 Windows Explorer window for the\f1  \b result\\bin\b0\f0  director\f1 y is\f0  also added to the Start menu when the source code is installed.\par
\par
Finally, if Wise for Windows Installer is installed, an installer for DFU Wizard and DFU Tool Tips can be built using the supplied \b .wsi\b0  file. The installer files are built to \b devHost\\Install\b0 . Shortcuts to both the \b .wsi\b0  file and the directory containing the installers are also added to the Start menu during installation of the source code if WfWI is detected.\par
\par
Note that the DFU Wizard application requires the SHFolder DLL to be installed on the target system. A freely distributable version of this DLL, obtained from the Microsoft Platform SDK, is included in the \b devHost\\Install\b0  directory as \b SHFolder.exe\b0 . This is included and installed as part of the DFU Wizard installer.\par
